article.headline: Green Bay 64, Detroit 62
article.story: DETROIT -- Rahmon Fletcher scored 16 points, including the go-ahead layup with about two minutes left, to lift Wiscosin-Green Bay to a 64-62 win over Detroit on Thursday night. Fletcher made it 61-60 with the fastbreak layup after teammate Seth Evans stole the ball from Detroit's Woody Payne with 2:11 to go. The Phoenix (16-10, 8-6 Horizon) then strengthened their lead with a free throw by Evans and two by Randy Berry to make it 64-60. Eli Holman sank a layup for the Titans (15-11, 7-7) with 42 seconds left, but that was as close as they would get. Another steal by Evans in the final seconds clinched the game for the Phoenix. Berry finished with 11 points for Green Bay, while Rian Pearson came off the bench to score 10. Evans added six. Thomas Kennedy and Chase Simon each scored 15 points for the Titans. Xavier Keeling added 14 points and grabbed 13 rebounds.
